cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.RO 

This paper belongs to the field of game theory and traffic simulation, which is most likely to be categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) as it introduces traffic lights into congestion games to reduce selfish routing inefficiencies. It also involves the use of simulation tools such as SUMO, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Additionally, the paper deals with network optimization and traffic flow, which could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
